metadata.name: Northwood
metadata.description:
Northwood...if they could. I couldn't help but stop when I was approaching this vacated motel on the side of the road. I grabbed my camera and walked around for a few minutes in curiosity. Hmm...no people, no cars...nothing. I noticed the sign was updated, but who was doing that? Maybe they were using it as a platform to "post." Oh well.

I looked for the best angle I could frame and snapped away. All politics aside, I feel as though this shot embodies more than just a photo, but a block of time where the world seemed so unsure about everything. Politics, Real Estate, Retail, Food, Hospitality, Travel...it was all up in the air and everything felt out-of-control.

The misleading information and poor guidance we are often given, leads to new minds thinking outside the box and clearing a path to a better future. Nothing is given, but is yours for the taking...
